  <his_func>&lt;p&gt;A.A. Brown (1732-1785) was a merchant in Veere (Zeeland). In June 1773 he became the fiscal of Essequibo. He had the right to investigate ships and plantations for clandestine import and export. He was also Councillor of the Council of Policy and he owned the 'De Philantropica' plantation. In the autumn of 1781 he returned to Veere.&lt;/p&gt;</his_func>
